-- Tianjin Companies Surge Most on Report City to Build Financial District
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-26T01:58:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/tianjin-companies-surge-most-on-report-city-to-build-financial-district.html

          
          
             Shares of Tianjin-based companies
surged today on the Shanghai exchange after a report that the
city may spend 200 billion yuan ($30 billion) to build a
financial district.  
 Tianjin Quanye Bazaar (Group) Co., which operates
department stores, jumped by the 10 percent daily limit to 5.90
yuan as of 9:46 a.m. local time. Dingsheng Tiangong Construction
Machinery Co. climbed by the limit to 10.89 yuan as Tianjin Hi-
Tech Development Co. rose 9.7 percent to 5.56 yuan.  
 Tianjin plans to build a financial district in the Binhai
New Area over 10 years, the China News Agency reported on its
website, citing a draft of plan.  
